The People of the State of Illinois, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. William Brown, Defendant-Appellant.(No. 59178;First District (5th Division)March 22, 1974.

BARRETT, J., took no part.

James J. Doherty, Public Defender, of Chicago (William Lebovitz, Assistant Public Defender, of counsel), for appellant.Bernard Carey, State’s Attorney, of Chicago (Kenneth L. Gillis and Mary Ellen Dienes, Assistant State’s Attorneys, of counsel), for the People. PER CURIAM.
